ome rest.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/YOrQU8X</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Will0099]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Can we please celebrate something?</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/RJ7esGb</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/rmJVYze.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Edit- jarod finally passed at 4:07pm Pacific.He can finally rest.

Yesterday I had to make yet another amazingly difficult decision. I had to let my 23 year old son go. Misdiagnosed with mental health issues for the past year, he in fact had an extremely aggressive and malignant brain tumor growing. By the time we discovered what was really really going on, it was too late. Inoperable. Untreatable. He is going to die in the next 48 hours. And there is nothing I can do to stop it.

I am here to tell you, right now, stop what you are doing. Take 30 seconds out of your busy work day. Call someone you love. Text them. Grab them as you pass by in the hall if you are WFH. Tell them you love them. Hug them tight. Let them know how important they are to you.

We are all busy. We all have jobs and spend hours a day toiling away. But it all means nothing when your child is intubated in an ICU and is going to die. And you can't do anything. Before all this went down, he told me how much he loved me. He told me how proud he was of me. And I told him. And then he was gone.

Make the time. Tomorrow may be too late. Take it from a father who has now lost two kids, and a son who has lost both parents. Work your work and hopefully love what you do, but be absolutely sure to put your family or your loved ones above everything.

Jarod Markus-Brooks, 1998-2022. I love you son. I will miss you dearly. I will honor your name by doing great things. Thank you for blessing me with your presence in my life.

I will celebrate your life by being a better person. I'm sending this out so that perhaps others may celebrate too.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/RJ7esGb</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[aceebrofb]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Baby Goat Tails</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/hnUPyUd</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/xcidqEw.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/hnUPyUd</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[SpottieOttieDopaliciousAngel]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>What an amazing experience.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/LvUH7jc</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/f7kVQQI.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Source : 
